                    "id": "blk_405",
                    "type": "content",
                    "title": "Speaking Clearly",
                    "body": "Use simple, direct language. Avoid jargon unless you're certain the other person understands it. Speak at a moderate pace - not too fast or too slow. Articulate your words clearly. Organize your thoughts before speaking on important matters."
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "blk_406",
                    "type": "content",
                    "title": "Written Communication",
                    "body": "For written messages, use proper grammar and punctuation. Keep messages concise and focused. Use bullet points for multiple items. Proofread before sending. Consider your tone - written messages can be easily misinterpreted without vocal cues."
